==Standard dialogue==
===Letting him cook===
*{{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Recipe for Disaster|event=no}}
* {{topt|Valentine's Day}}
** '''Player:''' Any plans for Valentine's Day, cook?
** '''Cook:''' I had plans for something, a little different for my girlfriend this year. You know, something less cliché.
** '''Player:''' So no midnight cruise along the isle of Crandor? No romantic meals at Gianne's cuisine?
** '''Cook:''' I'd like to keep it simple. Simple yet effective.
** '''Player:''' Cook her a meal?
** '''Cook:''' I did that last year and mixed up the sauces. Ended up pouring in some sauce I got from a Kebab seller in Pollnivneach. Safe to say, no love was shared that day.
** '''Player:''' How about a box of chocolate then?
** '''Cook:''' I said less cliché!
** '''Player:''' Chocolate strawberries?
** '''Cook:''' Ahah!
** '''Cook:''' Perfect! Simple, yet not painfully common or obvious. She won't be expecting that.
** '''Cook:''' Fetch me a bar of chocolate and I'll get to work. I'll even make you a box to give to your valentine.
** {{tact|end}}

===Sweet endorphins===
*{{tselect|Select an Option}}
* {{topt|Recipe for Disaster|event=no}}
* {{topt|Valentine's Day}}
** '''Cook:''' Have you got the chocolate?
** '''Player:''' I have some here.
** '''Cook:''' Excellent! Hand it over and give me a minute.
** '''Cook:''' There you go!
** {{tact|receives=a [[box of chocolate strawberries]]}} 
** '''Cook:''' Don't hog them all to yourself. Share them with your valentine, adventurer!
** '''Player:''' I will, thank you!
** {{tact|end}}

==Opening the box of chocolate strawberries==
===When opening a box received from the Lumbridge cook===
* {{tbox|The cook suggested I give these to someone else instead of just hogging them all to myself.}}
* {{tact|end}}

===When opening a box received from another player===
* {{tbox|To [player name], with love – Your secret admirer.}}
* {{tact|receives=three [[chocolate strawberries]]}}
* {{tact|end}}
